    "tiles": [
      {
        "id": "cQ1P58CF9CZfOr3U",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>To find out more about moths and other insects in your area, you are going to design an experiment, build a moth trap, and analyze your data. To help you design an experiment to answer your group&#x27;s questions from the Warmup, take a look at some data that Frieda took when she did her moth experiment. Copy this data into your Workspace and think about what you can learn from this data and what you can&#x27;t. How would you tell Frieda to change it? Can you graph it? How else could you look at it?</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "2tHAmBMyc1Uc_04V",
        "content": {
          "type": "DataCard"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "wPfWIe0oPG6SVoda",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>With your driving questions in hand and a good idea of the kind of data you will need to collect to make evidence-based claims about your answers (experimental design) you are ready to actually run a moth collection experiment. For that, you&#x27;ll need to build a moth trap. <a href=\"https://www.motheducation.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/MothEdTrapInstructions.pdf\">moth trap instructions </a>Once you and your group have conducted your experiments, make sure you put all your data into cards or a data table to explore it further.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "6qYjnd2J9gJPEmAN",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>ORGANIZE</strong></p><p>Think about organizing the moths into categories that will help answer your group&#x27;s research question.</p><p><strong>Would data cards or a table help you get organized? </strong></p>"
          ]
        }
      }
    ],
